  "elapsed_s": 8.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 15 SECONDS] In the late '30s, things-- after-- it must have been about 1936 I remember when Hitler came-- came to power after a year or two, he-- all the Jews that were of Polish-- a lot of Jews lived in Germany of Polish extraction, or Polish-Jewish extraction, and they were thrown out.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Nazis threw them onto the border between Poland and Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And at that time, we felt sorry for these people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In the papers, on the radio we heard that people being thrown out from their houses, from their businesses.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And little did we realize what's waiting for us because eventually, these people, they managed to get away.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Poland wouldn't let them in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So they were trapped on the border for months.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But eventually, they managed to get visas to different countries and they emigrated to different countries.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Lucky for them.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "If they would have stayed-- if Poland would have let them in, they would have ended up where we were ended up.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So for them, it was good that they didn't, that Poland didn't let them in.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That's how it worked out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And this carried on till 1938 when Hitler marched into Austria and then Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then we realized that war is coming.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But we were very heartened when England and France signed a Tripartite Pact with Poland, that if Poland is attacked, they will come to-- they will come to the Polish rescue.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we didn't know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We thought that Hitler-- after this pact was signed, we-- we were hoping that Hitler will not risk and go to war if he's-- if England and France are going to defend Poland.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
